#: ../../L/logical.rst:5
msgid "logical"
msgstr "logical"

#: ../../L/logical.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../L/logical.rst:9
msgid ""
"[from the technical term logical device, wherein a physical device is "
"referred to by an arbitrary ‘logical’ name] Having the role of. If a person "
"(say, Les Earnest at SAIL) who had long held a certain post left and were "
"replaced, the replacement would for a while be known as the logical Les "
"Earnest. (This does not imply any judgment on the replacement.) Compare "
":ref:`virtual`\\."
msgstr ""
"[物理デバイスが任意の‘論理’名で参照される論理デバイス(logical device)という専門用語から] "
"……の役割を持つこと。ある地位を長く保っていた人物(たとえばSAILのLes Earnest)が去って交代した場合、その後任はしばらくの間logical"
" Les Earnestとして知られることになる。(これは後任に対する何の判断も含意しない。)\\ :ref:`virtual`\\ と比較せよ。"

#: ../../L/logical.rst:14
msgid ""
"At Stanford, ‘logical’ compass directions denote a coordinate system "
"relative to El Camino Real, in which ‘logical north’ is always toward San "
"Francisco and ‘logical south’ is always toward San Jose--in spite of the "
"fact that El Camino Real runs physical north/south near San Francisco, "
"physical east/west near San Jose, and along a curve everywhere in between. "
"(The best rule of thumb here is that, by definition, El Camino Real always "
"runs logical north-south.)"
msgstr ""
"Stanfordでは、‘logical’な方位は、El Camino Realを基準とした座標系を表す。そこでは‘logical "
"north’は常にSan Francisco方向を、‘logical south’は常にSan Jose方向を指す——El Camino "
"RealがSan Francisco付近では物理的に南北に、San "
"Jose付近では物理的に東西に走り、その間のいたるところで曲線に沿って走るという事実にもかかわらず、である。(ここでの最良の経験則は、定義により、El "
"Camino Realは常にlogical north-southに走る、というものである。)"

#: ../../L/logical.rst:17
msgid ""
"In giving directions, one might say: \"To get to Rincon Tarasco restaurant, "
"get onto :ref:`El-Camino-Bignum` going logical north.\" Using the word "
"‘logical’ helps to prevent the recipient from worrying about that the fact "
"that the sun is setting almost directly in front of him. The concept is "
"reinforced by North American highways which are almost, but not quite, "
"consistently labeled with logical rather than physical directions. A similar"
" situation exists at MIT: Route 128 (famous for the electronics industry "
"that grew up along it) wraps roughly 3 quarters around Boston at a radius of"
" 10 miles, terminating near the coastline at each end. It would be most "
"precise to describe the two directions along this highway as ‘clockwise’ and"
" ‘counterclockwise’, but the road signs all say \"north\" and \"south\", "
"respectively. A hacker might describe these directions as logical north and "
"logical south, to indicate that they are conventional directions not "
"corresponding to the usual denotation for those words."
msgstr ""
"道案内をするとき、こう言うかもしれない。「Rincon Tarascoレストランに行くには、\\ :ref:`El-Camino-Bignum`\\ "
"に乗ってlogical "
"northへ向かえ。」‘logical’という語を使うことは、太陽がほとんど真正面に沈んでいるという事実を相手が気にしないように助ける。この概念は、ほとんど、だが完全にではないにせよ、一貫して物理的方向ではなく論理的方向で標識される北米の幹線道路によって補強される。同様の状況がMITにも存在する。Route"
" "
"128(沿線で成長した電子産業で有名)は、半径10マイルでBostonをおよそ4分の3周し、両端は海岸線近くで終わる。この幹線道路に沿った二つの方向を‘時計回り’と‘反時計回り’と表現するのが最も正確だろうが、道路標識はすべてそれぞれ「north」と「south」と書いている。ハッカーは、これらが普通のその語の意味に対応しない慣習上の方向であることを示すために、これらの方向をlogical"
" northとlogical southと表現するかもしれない。"
